def binary_search(arr, left, right, x):
    if right >= left:
        mid = left + (right - left) // 2
        if arr[mid] == x:
            return mid
        elif arr[mid] > x:
            return binary_search(arr, left, mid - 1, x)
        else:
            return binary_search(arr, mid + 1, right, x)
    else:
        return -1
```

In the above function, if the middle element is greater than x, the function will continue to search in the left half of the array (from left to mid-1). If the middle element is less than x, the function will continue to search in the right half of the array (from mid + 1 to right). If neither of the above conditions are met, it means the element is not present in the array and thus, -1 is returned.

